Class SSLActiveMQMultipartyCommunicationSetup

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MultipartyCommunicationSetup

    public class SSLActiveMQMultipartyCommunicationSetup
extends ActiveMQMultipartyCommunicationSetup
    This implementation uses ssl protocol in the multiparty JMS queue communication using the ActiveMQ implementation.
    Author:
    Cryptography and Computer Security Research Group Department of Computer Science Bar-Ilan University (Moriya Farbstein)

      • SSLActiveMQMultipartyCommunicationSetup

        public SSLActiveMQMultipartyCommunicationSetup(java.lang.String url,
                                       java.util.List<PartyData> parties,
                                       java.lang.String storePass)
                                        throws DuplicatePartyException,
                                               javax.net.ssl.SSLException,
                                               java.io.IOException
        A constructor that create an SSLActiveMQCommunicationSetup object between the current application and any other party in the protocol. It uses the default key store and trust store.
        Parameters:
        url - The url of the ActiveMQ broker.
        parties - List of parties to communicate with. The first party in the list represents the current application.
        storePass - The password for the key store and trust store.
        Throws:
        DuplicatePartyException - In case there are two identical parties.
        java.io.IOException - In case there is a problem with the key store or trust store file.
        javax.net.ssl.SSLException - In case there is a problem during the SSL protocol initialization.

        A constructor that create an SSLActiveMQCommunicationSetup object between the current application and any other party in the protocol. It uses the default key store and trust store.
        Parameters:
        url - The url of the ActiveMQ broker.
        parties - List of parties to communicate with. The first party in the list represents the current application.
        storePass - The password for the key store and trust store.
        enableNagle - Indicates if to use Nagle's algorithm or not. For cryptographic algorithms it is much better to disable Nagle's algorithm.
